            <p>Rev. Dr Morais&#44;<lb/>
                Philadelphia.<lb/>
                Dear Sir&#44;<lb/></p>
            <p>The &#34;Toronto Hebrew Cong<hi rend="sup">n</hi>&#34; is adver<lb/>&#45;tising for &#34;Chazan&#44; Reader&#44; Teacher&#44; Lecturer<lb/> &#40;English&#41;&#45;&#45;one capable of leading a choir<lb/> preferred&#34; &#38; has received an applicat<hi rend="sup">b</hi> from<lb/> Rev Herman Phillips&#44; Boston&#44; who refers<lb/> us to you.  We should&#44; therefore&#44; esteem it<lb/> a favour&#44; if you would kindly give us<lb/> some informat<hi rend="sup">n</hi> regarding his abilities&#44;<lb/> character &#38;c &#38;c.  Apologising for troubling<lb/> you.  Yours very truly&#44;<lb/> Alfred D. Benjamin<lb/> Prest<lb/></p>
            <p>As a meeting of the Cong<hi rend="sup">n</hi> is convened for<lb/> next Sunday&#44; please reply by <hi rend="underline">return of mail</hi><lb/> &#38; greatly oblige.<lb/></p>
